import subprocess
import sys
import os

# This code, when run in a cell, will open a *new* terminal window
# that runs the interactive launcher script.
# The cell itself will finish executing almost instantly, avoiding a timeout.

# Define the command to launch the script in a new terminal
# This works for Windows (cmd), macOS (Terminal), and Linux (x-terminal-emulator)
if os.name == 'nt': # For Windows
    command = [
        'cmd.exe', '/c', 'start', 'cmd.exe', '/k',
        sys.executable, 'specification_runner_launcher.py'
    ]
else: # For macOS and Linux
    # This command may need adjustment depending on the default terminal emulator
    command = [
        'x-terminal-emulator', '-e',
        f'bash -c "{sys.executable} specification_runner_launcher.py; exec bash"'
    ]

# Use Popen to launch the new terminal without waiting for it to complete.
try:
    subprocess.Popen(command)
    print("Launcher script initiated in a new terminal window.")
except FileNotFoundError:
    print("Error: Could not find a terminal to launch the script.")
    print("Please ensure you have a default terminal configured (e.g., x-terminal-emulator on Linux).")
